    <note>Gu(3) Zongming [19390] He is identified as an East Lake (Dong Hu) person in Yuan(1) Xie's [10289] funerary inscription for his great grandson, Yixian [19393] (q.v.). He was a friend of Xie's great grandfather, Yuan(1) Shao [10231], with whom he traveled after Shao was purged during the period of Cai(1) Jing's [1649] administration. My guess is that he was a son of Lin [935], but there is no documentary evidence to support this hypothesis. All three Shaoxing Gu(3) are probably members of the same root lineage. For now, however, I am treating them as three different lineages.</note>
